The use of scaled dimension and its rescalings suggests a connection to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these concepts are often used in the analysis of algorithms. The paper also involves logical reasoning and proof techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The mention of BPP != EXP and P != PSPACE suggests a connection to the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory), as these are important open problems in the field. Finally, the mention of ESPACE (exponential space) suggests a connection to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as space complexity is often relevant to cryptographic protocols.
